Italy helped Beijing build a solar energy system for the Olympic Games in 2008 and beyond. China plans to spend $180 billion on renewable energy, including substantial solar heat development. Indonesia plans to build thousands of small solar power units to boost power capacity. Taiwan's renewable energy promotion has yielded the world's third highest installation density of solar water heaters. Angola developed a plan to supply energy to its rural population. The plan would provide 1300 villages with 15 solar generating plants each. 